cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.HC 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with recognizing group activities from video data. The use of deep learning models such as LSTM also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The evaluation of the proposed model on two datasets, including a new volleyball dataset, suggests that it could also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the focus on understanding human-level information for whole activity recognition suggests that it could belong to the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category.
